article.description: Anderson helps TCU turn back Bradley 57-49
article.headline: Anderson helps TCU turn back Bradley 57-49
article.linkText: Anderson helps TCU turn back Bradley 57-49
article.story: CORPUS CHRISTI, Texas -- Kyan Anderson overcame a poor-shooting night by hitting four free throws in the closing seconds Saturday night and Texas Christian held on to beat Bradley 57-49 at the Corpus Christi Coast Classic. Anderson made just 1 of his 10 shots but went 8 of 8 from the foul line for the Horned Frogs (6-0), who made 25 of 33 free throws. Auston Barnes had 19 points for Bradley (2-3). TCU used baskets by Hudson Price and Anderson to open the second half to build a 35-24 lead but Josh Cunningham scored twice for Bradley to get it back to single digits, 35-28 with 15:42 to play. The game stayed close the rest of the way. Warren Jones knocked down a 3-poitner midway through the second half, giving Bradley a 42-41 lead. TCU broke away from a 44-44 tie with seven-straight points, capped by a 3 from Kenrich Williams. The first half was a parade to the foul line. TCU made 12 of 17 free throws to 12 of 21 for Bradley. Bradley made just 27.8 percent from the field, going 5 of 18, while TCU was 9 of 22. TCU got the lead to double figures, 26-16 on an Amric Fields jumper at 3:47 and pushed it to 13 but a Barnes 3 just before the buzzer made it 31-24 at the break. In the second half Bradley was perfect on its three free throws while TCU was 13 of 16. Warren Jones added 10 points for Bradley, which had a 32-27 rebounding advantage, led by Josh Cunningham's 12. Williams also had 10 points for TCU, which was just 2 of 16 from behind the arc. TIP-INS TCU: The Frogs are off to their best start since going 9-0 to begin the 1997-98 campaign, which also happens to be the last time TCU made the NCAA Tournament. ... Both TCU 3's were by reserves, Hudson Price and Kenrich Williams. Kyan Anderson was 0-8 behind the arc. ... TCU was out-rebounded for the first time this season. The 27 rebounds were 15 below their average. Bradley: This was the Braves' first road game of the season. The Braves have now lost five straight road games and are winless in their last 11 games played at a neutral site. ... Three of Bradley's first five games have been against Texas schools. The Braves opened the season with an 86-75 loss to UT-Arlington and dropped Texas A&M-Corpus Christi, 58-32, Tuesday. UP NEXT TCU plays the Mississippi State for the title. Bradley faces Saint Louis in the game for third place.
